Figure 7:Qualitative ablation study.Given the source scene (a) and the editing task (b), our full method (c) produces a coherent result.
Removing Sync-Attention (d) leads to incomplete material modification;
removing View-Aware Weighting (e) introduces boundary noise and artifacts near occluded regions;
removing the Residual Head (f) causes subtle distortion in static background areas.
